>> [ GRUNTS ]

03:55.944 --> 03:59.322
THANK YOU. THANK YOU ALL.

03:59.447 --> 04:00.281
[ CHUCKLES ]

04:00.407 --> 04:02.201
NEVER THOUGHT THE TRIANGLE WOULD

04:02.325 --> 04:02.868
GET ME.

04:02.993 --> 04:03.535
[ LAUGHS ]

04:03.660 --> 04:04.452
>> [ CHUCKLES ]

04:04.578 --> 04:05.537
YEAH, THE TRIANGLE.

04:05.662 --> 04:06.287
THAT'S --

04:06.413 --> 04:07.539
>> [ CLEARS THROAT ]

04:07.664 --> 04:10.042
>> ONE POSSIBLE EXPLANATION.

04:10.167 --> 04:11.710
>> WHATEVER HAPPENED OUT THERE,

04:11.835 --> 04:13.212
CAPTAIN WILD, WE'RE HAPPY WE

04:13.336 --> 04:14.171
COULD HELP.

04:14.295 --> 04:15.380
>> YOU KNOW, HOW ABOUT A QUICK

04:15.505 --> 04:16.631
CHECKUP AT THE HOSPITAL,

04:16.757 --> 04:17.591
CAPTAIN?

04:17.716 --> 04:18.675
FREE HELICOPTER RIDE IN IT FOR

04:18.800 --> 04:21.845
YOU.

04:21.970 --> 04:22.846
[ BANGING ]

04:22.971 --> 04:23.805
>> TRIANGLE?

04:23.931 --> 04:25.515
>> THE GRIFFIN ROCK TRIANGLE.

04:25.640 --> 04:27.059
DOZENS OF BOATS HAVE GONE

04:27.184 --> 04:28.018
MISSING THERE.

04:28.143 --> 04:29.770
THEY SAY IT'S BEEN HAPPENING

04:29.895 --> 04:30.729
FOR CENTURIES.

04:30.854 --> 04:32.022
>> THAT'S JUST AN OLD

04:32.147 --> 04:33.107
FISHERMAN'S TALE.

04:33.232 --> 04:34.858
>> PERHAPS, BUT I DO REMEMBER A

04:34.983 --> 04:36.276
COUPLE OF PLEASURE BOATS

04:36.401 --> 04:38.528
DISAPPEARING WHEN I WAS A BOY.

04:38.653 --> 04:40.155
NEVER FOUND ANY SIGN OF

04:40.280 --> 04:41.448
WRECKAGE, THOUGH.

04:41.573 --> 04:42.950
>> HMM. HULL'S INTACT.

04:43.075 --> 04:44.785
NO REASON IT SHOULD HAVE SUNK

04:44.910 --> 04:46.870
LIKE IT DID.

05:04.972 --> 05:07.682
>> IT LOOKS LIKE A SEA MONSTER,

05:07.808 --> 05:08.683
OR --

05:08.809 --> 05:10.018
>> SEA MONSTER?

05:10.144 --> 05:12.353
THERE ARE MONSTERS IN THE SEA?

05:12.479 --> 05:14.856
WHY AM I ONLY HEARING ABOUT THIS

05:14.982 --> 05:15.482
NOW?

05:15.607 --> 05:16.858
I WAS OUT THERE!

05:16.984 --> 05:18.526
>> THEY'RE JUST A MYTH, BLADES.

05:18.652 --> 05:19.820
>> LIKE THE GRIFFIN ROCK

05:19.945 --> 05:20.821
TRIANGLE'S A MYTH.

05:20.946 --> 05:22.530
I HAVE A SORE ROTOR BEARING THAT

05:22.656 --> 05:23.490
SAYS OTHERWISE.

05:23.615 --> 05:24.950
>> PERHAPS IT WOULD BE PRUDENT

05:25.075 --> 05:26.367
TO POST SEA-MONSTER WARNING

05:26.493 --> 05:27.452
SIGNS IN THAT AREA.

05:27.577 --> 05:29.037
>> I JUST HOPE WE'RE DONE WITH

05:29.163 --> 05:30.205
THE OCEAN FOR A WHILE.

05:30.330 --> 05:32.373
THE SALT'S CHAFING MY CHASSIS.

05:32.499 --> 05:34.417
>> BUT HOW DO YOU KNOW WHAT'S

05:34.542 --> 05:36.003
MYTH AND WHAT'S REAL?

05:36.128 --> 05:37.462
>> IF THIS PLATE CAME FROM A

05:37.587 --> 05:38.922
SHIP THAT WENT DOWN IN THAT

05:39.047 --> 05:40.548
AREA, IT COULD BE PROOF THAT THE

05:40.674 --> 05:41.716
TRIANGLE EXISTS.

05:41.842 --> 05:45.720
TIME FOR A LITTLE RESEARCH.

05:45.846 --> 05:49.057
[ ELECTRICITY BUZZES ]

05:49.183 --> 05:50.391
[ COMPUTER BEEPS ]

05:50.517 --> 05:52.602
>> AN IMPRESSIVE FIND INDEED.

05:52.727 --> 05:54.980
>> BUT, DAD, YOU ALWAYS SAID THE

05:55.105 --> 05:56.648
TRIANGLE WAS HOGWASH.

05:56.773 --> 05:58.566
>> TRUE, BUT OCCASIONALLY WHEN

05:58.692 --> 06:00.568
YOU WASH A HOG, YOU DISCOVER IT

06:00.694 --> 06:02.445
WAS NEVER A HOG TO BEGIN WITH.

06:02.570 --> 06:05.615
LET'S SEE WHAT WE CAN UNCOVER.

06:05.740 --> 06:06.616
FOUND A MATCH.

06:06.741 --> 06:07.701
SOMETHING CALLED

06:07.826 --> 06:11.205
PROJECT MIDGARD -- 28 YEARS AGO.

06:11.330 --> 06:14.373
MIDGARD, MID-- OH, OF COURSE,

06:14.499 --> 06:15.709
NORSE MYTHOLOGY.

06:15.834 --> 06:17.961
THE MIDGARD SERPENT WAS SAID TO

06:18.086 --> 06:19.504
ENCIRCLE THE WORLD.

06:19.629 --> 06:20.922
>> BUT WHAT IS THE

06:21.048 --> 06:22.216
MIDGARD PROJECT?

06:22.341 --> 06:24.051
>> NO IDEA, AND THE ONLY

06:24.176 --> 06:26.220
INFORMATION HERE IS A CODE --

06:26.345 --> 06:28.387
C-638.

06:28.513 --> 06:30.557
>> THAT SOUNDS LIKE A REFERENCE

06:30.682 --> 06:34.895
NUMBER FROM THE ARCHIVES.

06:35.020 --> 06:38.899
>> HERE'S AISLE "C."

06:39.024 --> 06:41.568
638! THIS IS IT!

06:41.693 --> 06:43.904
>> WELL?

06:44.029 --> 06:45.030
>> WHAT IS IT?

06:45.155 --> 06:46.489
>> A FILM CANISTER.

06:46.614 --> 06:48.616
MY DAD HAS SOME, ONLY SMALLER,

06:48.742 --> 06:50.285
FROM WHEN HE WAS A KID.

06:50.409 --> 06:51.953
>> WELL, FILM IS SO LAST

06:52.079 --> 06:52.871
CENTURY.

06:52.996 --> 06:54.622
WHAT DOES IT HAVE TO DO WITH

06:54.748 --> 06:55.414
MIDGARD?

06:55.540 --> 06:56.750
>> MOVIE NIGHT!

06:56.875 --> 06:57.751
[ FILM PROJECTOR CLICKS ]

06:57.876 --> 07:01.755
[ BEEP ]

07:01.880 --> 07:04.258
>>  LOG ENTRY 001.

07:04.383 --> 07:06.093
PROFESSOR ANNA BARANOVA.

07:06.218 --> 07:07.594
DESPITE THE COUNCIL'S

07:07.719 --> 07:09.637
SKEPTICISM, PROJECT MIDGARD HS

07:09.763 --> 07:11.348
BEEN OFFICIALLY APPROVED.

07:11.472 --> 07:13.225
WE NOW BEGIN CONSTRUCTION OF

07:13.350 --> 07:15.227
THE MIDGARD ITSELF -- A MOBILE

07:15.352 --> 07:17.271
UNDERWATER LABORATORY THAT WIL

07:17.396 --> 07:19.314
LAUNCH FROM TUNNEL 15.

07:19.439 --> 07:21.566
I KNOW WHAT'S BEING SAID, BUTI

07:21.691 --> 07:22.817
AM NOT A FOOL.

07:22.943 --> 07:24.903
THE GRIFFIN ROCK TRIANGLE IS

07:25.028 --> 07:27.239
VERY REAL.

07:27.364 --> 07:29.324
I'VE SEEN IT TAKE DOWN A SHIP

07:29.449 --> 07:30.992
IN LESS THAN A MINUTE.

07:31.118 --> 07:33.036
AND, THROUGH SCIENCE, I WILL

07:33.161 --> 07:34.495
DISCOVER THE TRUTH.

07:34.621 --> 07:35.663
[ BEEP ]

07:35.789 --> 07:36.664
[ FILM PROJECTOR SHUTS OFF ]

07:36.790 --> 07:38.666
>> MYSTERY SOLVED.

07:38.792 --> 07:39.834
WELL DONE, CODY.

07:39.960 --> 07:41.878
>> BUT WHAT HAPPENED TO HER LAB?

07:42.003 --> 07:43.880
>> WELL, I IMAGINE IT WAS NEVER

07:44.005 --> 07:44.839
BUILT.

07:44.965 --> 07:46.383
IF BARANOVA HAD CONDUCTED ANY

07:46.507 --> 07:48.051
RESEARCH WHATSOEVER, THE DETAILS

07:48.176 --> 07:49.386
WOULD HAVE COME UP IN THE

07:49.510 --> 07:50.762
COMPUTER SEARCH.

07:56.226 --> 07:57.727
>> I DON'T KNOW, CODY.

07:57.852 --> 07:59.729
THIS IS LIKE SEARCHING FOR A

07:59.854 --> 08:01.398
NEEDLE IN A STACK OF...

08:01.522 --> 08:02.899
OTHER NEEDLES.

08:03.024 --> 08:04.734
>>  WHY WOULD YOU STACK NEEDLES?

08:04.859 --> 08:05.735
>> [ SCOFFS ]

08:05.860 --> 08:07.446
MY POINT IS, IT'S IMPOSSIBLE TO

08:07.570 --> 08:09.072
FIND ANYTHING MARKED "15" IN

08:09.197 --> 08:11.158
THIS MAZE DOWN HERE.

08:15.120 --> 08:16.121
I'M SORRY, BUD.

08:16.246 --> 08:18.081
WE'VE BEEN AT THIS FOR HOURS.

08:18.206 --> 08:18.915
[ BEEP ]

08:19.040 --> 08:19.666
OKAY, GUYS, WE'RE DONE.

08:19.791 --> 08:21.376
MEET AT THE JUNCTION.

08:25.546 --> 08:26.631
[ ENGINE SHUTS OFF ]

08:26.756 --> 08:28.175
>> FIND ANYTHING AT ALL?

08:28.300 --> 08:30.135
>> NOT UNLESS YOU'RE LOOKING FOR

08:30.260 --> 08:31.719
TUNNEL "V," "X," OR "I."

08:31.845 --> 08:32.679
>> WAIT.

08:32.804 --> 08:34.264
YOU FOUND TUNNELS MARKED WITH

08:34.389 --> 08:35.140
LETTERS?

08:35.265 --> 08:38.477
THOSE WERE ROMAN NUMERALS!

08:38.601 --> 08:41.146
"X" IS 10, AND "V" IS 5.

08:41.271 --> 08:43.190
SEE? 15.

08:43.315 --> 08:45.233
>> I STILL DON'T UNDERSTAND.

08:45.359 --> 08:47.610
THE ROMANS DUG THESE TUNNELS ALL

08:47.735 --> 08:49.737
THE WAY TO GRIFFIN ROCK FROM

08:49.863 --> 08:50.571
ITALY?

08:50.697 --> 08:53.533
NOW, THAT'S JUST SILLY.

09:01.958 --> 09:05.712
>> WHOA.

09:15.638 --> 09:17.474
>> PROFESSOR BARANOVA APPARENTLY

09:17.598 --> 09:19.100
GOT AS FAR AS BUILDING HER

09:19.226 --> 09:20.768
MOORING STATION.

09:20.894 --> 09:22.770
IMPRESSIVE.

09:22.896 --> 09:25.815
[ ALARM BEEPING ]

09:25.940 --> 09:28.860
>>  DOCKING PROTOCOL INITIATED.

09:44.501 --> 09:46.711
[ ALL GRUNTING ]

09:46.836 --> 09:50.424
>> LET'S KNOCK IT DOWN!

09:51.508 --> 09:53.718
[ ALL GRUNTING ]

09:53.843 --> 09:55.762
>> THE COMPUTER MUST THINK THE

09:55.887 --> 09:57.138
MIDGARD IS DOCKING.

09:57.264 --> 09:58.473
>> CAN'T YOU FIX IT?

09:58.598 --> 10:00.392
>> LOOK FOR AN EMERGENCY

10:00.517 --> 10:01.309
OVERRIDE.

10:01.435 --> 10:04.896
SOME KIND OF BUTTON OR LEVER.

10:06.773 --> 10:11.819
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]

10:11.945 --> 10:13.863
[ METAL CREAKING ]

10:21.121 --> 10:24.124
[ BOTH PANTING ]

10:26.626 --> 10:28.253
PUMPS ARE DRAINING THE WATER.

10:28.378 --> 10:30.130
AMAZING THESE SYSTEMS ARE STILL

10:30.255 --> 10:31.047
OPERATIONAL.

10:31.172 --> 10:32.466
>> EXCEPT FOR THE PART WHERE

10:32.591 --> 10:33.716
THEY TRIED TO DROWN US.

10:33.841 --> 10:35.885
[ BANGING ON DOOR ]

10:36.010 --> 10:37.053
[ ALL GRUNT ]

10:37.178 --> 10:38.263
>> WHOA, WHOA.

10:38.388 --> 10:40.223
>> WE'RE OKAY. WE'RE FINE.

10:40.348 --> 10:41.516
>> THIS MISSION'S OVER.

10:41.641 --> 10:43.184
>> IT'S TOO DANGEROUS DOWN HERE.

10:43.310 --> 10:44.852
>> I SUGGEST TUNNEL 15 BE SEALED

10:44.978 --> 10:45.812
OFF.

10:45.937 --> 10:46.813
I HAVE HAZARD TAPE IN MY GLOVE

10:46.938 --> 10:47.688
BOX.

10:47.814 --> 10:48.565
>> THEY'RE RIGHT, CODY.

10:48.689 --> 10:50.233
WE SHOULDN'T BE DOWN HERE, AT

10:50.358 --> 10:52.611
LEAST NOT ALONE.

10:52.735 --> 10:54.695
>> GUYS, WE CAME ALL THIS WAY.

10:54.821 --> 10:56.864
WE SHOULD AT LEAST LOOK AROUND.

10:56.990 --> 10:58.074
>> AND WE WILL.

10:58.199 --> 11:00.201
WE'LL PUT TOGETHER A TEAM, SOME

11:00.327 --> 11:01.536
EQUIPMENT, AND --

11:01.661 --> 11:02.537
[ GASPS ]

11:02.662 --> 11:03.830
>> DON'T PUSH ANY MORE BUTTONS!

11:03.955 --> 11:04.581
>> NO!

11:04.705 --> 11:06.333
>> CEASE AND DESIST!

11:06.458 --> 11:07.208
>> [ CHUCKLES ]

11:07.334 --> 11:08.460
LOOKS LIKE THE PROFESSOR

11:08.585 --> 11:10.629
UPGRADED TO VIDEO.

11:10.753 --> 11:12.922
>> AND AT THE BASE OF THE OCEAN

11:13.047 --> 11:15.091
TRENCH, A NATURALLY OCCURRING

11:15.216 --> 11:16.217
METHANE VENT.

11:16.343 --> 11:18.178
THE VENT PERIODICALLY RELEASES

11:18.303 --> 11:20.054
METHANE IN A MASSIVE BUBBLING

11:20.180 --> 11:22.056
PLUME THAT DISRUPTS THE WATER'S

11:22.182 --> 11:25.226
SURFACE ENOUGH TO SINK SHIPS.

11:25.352 --> 11:27.604
THE GRIFFIN ROCK TRIANGLE.

11:29.105 --> 11:32.150
SO, HOW DO WE STOP IT?

11:32.275 --> 11:34.027
AN EXPLOSIVE DROPPED INTO THE

11:34.152 --> 11:35.945
VENT SHOULD BRING TONS OF ROCK

11:36.070 --> 11:37.614
RAINING DOWN, SEALING THE

11:37.738 --> 11:38.948
METHANE IN FOREVER.

11:39.073 --> 11:41.201
THE SEA WOULD BE SAFE AGAIN.

11:41.326 --> 11:43.578
I KNOW THE COUNCIL WOULD NEVER

11:43.702 --> 11:45.997
ALLOW SUCH A MISSION, SO I HAVE

11:46.122 --> 11:48.500
DECIDED TO PROCEED  WITHOUT  THEIR

11:48.625 --> 11:50.669
APPROVAL OR KNOWLEDGE.

11:50.793 --> 11:53.505
I DEPART IN THE MORNING.

11:53.630 --> 11:56.508
[ STATIC ]

11:56.633 --> 11:58.635
>> I MET THE PROFESSOR ONCE.

11:58.759 --> 12:00.887
I REMEMBER HER BEING BRIGHT BUT

12:01.012 --> 12:01.888
GUARDED.

12:02.013 --> 12:03.682
THEN SHE DISAPPEARED.

12:03.806 --> 12:05.975
PEOPLE THOUGHT SHE JUST LEFT

12:06.100 --> 12:08.102
TOWN, BUT DIDN'T KNOW WHY.

12:08.228 --> 12:09.062
>>  NOW  WE DO.

12:09.187 --> 12:11.064
SHE BUILT THE MIDGARD AND TOOK

12:11.189 --> 12:12.315
IT INTO THE TRENCH.

12:12.440 --> 12:13.900
>> BUT THE VENT IS STILL

12:14.025 --> 12:15.151
RELEASING METHANE?

12:15.276 --> 12:17.153
>> THAT TELLS ME THAT BARANOVA'S

12:17.278 --> 12:18.363
THEORY WAS WRONG.

12:18.488 --> 12:19.489
>> OR SHE FAILED.

12:19.614 --> 12:20.948
EITHER WAY, CASE CLOSED.

12:21.074 --> 12:22.075
>> IT ISN'T CLOSED.

12:22.200 --> 12:23.368
WE STILL DON'T KNOW WHAT

12:23.493 --> 12:23.993
HAPPENED.

12:24.118 --> 12:24.994
>> CODY'S RIGHT.

12:25.119 --> 12:26.621
WE SHOULD AT LEAST VENTURE INTO

12:26.745 --> 12:28.289
THE TRENCH TO LOOK FOR WRECKAGE.

12:28.415 --> 12:29.207
>> I AGREE.

12:29.332 --> 12:31.084
IT'S THE LEAST WE COULD DO.

12:31.209 --> 12:32.544
WE'LL LEAVE AT DAWN.

12:32.669 --> 12:35.630
>> UGH. DAWN.

12:38.216 --> 12:40.260
>> I JUST GOT ALL THE SALT WATER

12:40.385 --> 12:42.178
OUT.

12:43.888 --> 12:46.600
>> WHAT -- WHAT IF IT ISN'T

12:46.725 --> 12:47.517
METHANE?

12:47.642 --> 12:48.851
WHAT IF IT IS A SEA MONSTER?

12:48.976 --> 12:50.937
ANYBODY THINK OF THAT!

12:55.233 --> 12:57.818
>> SO BEAUTIFUL.

13:09.581 --> 13:10.624
>>  SIR?

13:10.749 --> 13:12.584
>> I SEE IT, BUT IT COULD BE

13:12.709 --> 13:13.501
ANYTHING.

13:13.627 --> 13:15.336
>> OR IT COULD BE WRECKAGE.

13:15.462 --> 13:16.630
>>  SHALL WE INVESTIGATE, SIR?

13:16.755 --> 13:17.796
THE LEDGE APPEARS STABLE

13:17.922 --> 13:18.715
ENOUGH.

13:18.839 --> 13:20.174
>> THAT'S WHAT WE CAME FOR.

13:39.569 --> 13:41.946
>> I KNEW IT.

13:42.071 --> 13:43.281
>> UNBELIEVABLE.

13:43.406 --> 13:45.659
IT'S JUST BEEN SITTING DOWN HERE

13:45.784 --> 13:47.327
FOR 28 YEARS.

13:47.452 --> 13:48.995
>> THIS WAS WORTH GETTING OUT OF

13:49.120 --> 13:50.246
BED FOR.

13:55.460 --> 13:58.379
[ CREAKING ]

14:06.763 --> 14:08.014
>> SEA MONSTER!

14:08.139 --> 14:08.889
>> HUH?

14:09.015 --> 14:12.059
>> WHAT?

14:12.185 --> 14:13.561
>> I SAW IT, TOO.

14:13.687 --> 14:14.729
IT LOOKED LIKE --

14:14.853 --> 14:16.439
OH, BUT THAT CAN'T BE.

14:19.609 --> 14:22.069
>> [ GRUNTING ]

14:34.332 --> 14:37.377
[ DOOR CREAKS ]

14:37.502 --> 14:39.879
[ ALL GASP ]

14:40.004 --> 14:44.718
>> IDENTIFY YOURSELVES, NOW!

14:44.843 --> 14:46.553
>> PROFESSOR BARANOVA?

14:46.678 --> 14:47.512
>> WHAT?

14:47.637 --> 14:51.391
>> RESCUE BOTS, VEHICLE MODE.

14:51.516 --> 14:53.893
SORRY ABOUT THE FRIGHT, MA'AM.

14:54.018 --> 14:55.978
I'M CHIEF CHARLIE BURNS.

14:56.103 --> 14:57.480
THIS IS MY FAMILY.

14:57.605 --> 14:59.232
AND THESE ROBOTS ARE THE LATEST

14:59.357 --> 15:00.941
IN SEARCH-AND-RESCUE EQUIPMENT.

15:01.067 --> 15:03.611
>> WHAT? RESCUE?

15:03.737 --> 15:05.446
I-I DON'T KNOW WHETHER TO LAUGH

15:05.572 --> 15:08.783
OR -- NO, NO. NO, THANK YOU.

15:08.908 --> 15:11.452
>> WOW. OKAY, THEN.

15:11.578 --> 15:12.912
WELL, NICE MEETING YOU.

15:13.037 --> 15:13.954
LET'S HEAD HOME.

15:14.080 --> 15:16.082
>> KADE, THIS WOMEN'S BEEN ALONE

15:16.207 --> 15:17.667
DOWN HERE FOR 28 YEARS.

15:17.792 --> 15:19.043
CUT HER SOME SLACK.

15:19.168 --> 15:21.212
>> 28 YEARS?

15:21.337 --> 15:23.715
IT'S REALLY BEEN THAT LONG.

15:23.840 --> 15:27.218
YOU ARE R-REAL, AREN'T YOU?

15:27.343 --> 15:28.386
OF COURSE YOU ARE.

15:28.511 --> 15:30.179
EVEN  I  COULDN'T DREAM UP THOSE

15:30.304 --> 15:32.223
THINGS.

15:32.348 --> 15:35.059
I'M SORRY TO BE SO RUDE.

15:35.184 --> 15:40.106
PLEASE, COME IN.

15:41.858 --> 15:44.110
>> AT EASE...ROBOTS.

15:46.195 --> 15:48.030
>> DOESN'T WANT TO BE RESCUED?

15:48.155 --> 15:49.616
WHY DID WE EVEN BOTHER?

15:49.741 --> 15:51.158
>> SHE'D MISS HER HOME.

15:51.284 --> 15:52.993
IF ANYONE SHOULD UNDERSTAND

15:53.119 --> 15:55.663
THAT, IT'S US.

15:55.789 --> 15:57.039
>> HMM.

15:59.125 --> 16:03.170
>> THIS IS AMAZING!

16:03.296 --> 16:05.214
>> WHOA.

16:08.676 --> 16:11.387
>> YOU GUYS, LOOK.

16:11.512 --> 16:13.097
I FOUND ONE JUST LIKE IT.

16:13.222 --> 16:15.099
THAT'S HOW WE TRACKED YOU DOWN.

16:15.224 --> 16:16.810
>> CODY IS NOTHING IF NOT

16:16.935 --> 16:17.727
TENACIOUS.

16:17.852 --> 16:21.856
>> PROFESSOR, WHAT HAPPENED?

16:24.066 --> 16:25.443
>> I WAS PILOTING THE STATION

16:25.568 --> 16:27.027
OVER THE TRENCH, ABOUT TO DROP

16:27.153 --> 16:28.571
THE EXPLOSIVE DEVICE THAT WOULD

16:28.696 --> 16:29.864
SEAL UP THE METHANE VENT

16:29.989 --> 16:33.242
FOREVER, BUT JUST AT THAT MOMENT

16:33.367 --> 16:36.746
THERE WAS AN ERUPTION.

16:36.871 --> 16:39.457
I STRUCK THE EDGE OF THE CLIFF

16:39.582 --> 16:41.960
AND SLID DOWN TO THIS LEDGE,

16:42.084 --> 16:45.296
RUPTURING THE STARBOARD PODS.

16:45.421 --> 16:48.675
[ ALARM BEEPING ]

16:48.800 --> 16:50.677
THANKFULLY, I WAS ABLE TO SEAL

16:50.802 --> 16:52.386
OFF THE DAMAGED AREAS AND

16:52.512 --> 16:54.514
PREVENT FURTHER FLOODING, BUT MY

16:54.639 --> 16:56.557
ENGINES AND COMMUNICATION ARRAY

16:56.683 --> 16:59.226
WERE BEYOND REPAIR.

16:59.352 --> 17:01.562
I WAS TRAPPED.

17:01.688 --> 17:03.731
FORTUNATELY, THE GREENHOUSE AND

17:03.857 --> 17:05.692
LIFE-SUPPORT SYSTEMS REMAINED

17:05.817 --> 17:06.693
FUNCTIONAL.

17:06.818 --> 17:08.736
I'D FULLY EXPECTED NEVER TO SEE

17:08.862 --> 17:10.530
ANOTHER HUMAN BEING AGAIN.

17:10.655 --> 17:12.031
>> YOU'RE LUCKY THE EXPLOSIVE

17:12.156 --> 17:13.324
YOU WERE CARRYING DIDN'T

17:13.449 --> 17:13.992
DETONATE.

17:14.116 --> 17:15.994
>> YES.

17:16.118 --> 17:18.120
THE INCENDIARY DEVICE IS STILL

17:18.245 --> 17:20.206
OPERATIONAL, THOUGH THE LAUNCH

17:20.331 --> 17:22.000
TUBE DID SUSTAIN DAMAGE.

17:22.124 --> 17:23.710
THE ONLY WAY TO GET THE DEVICE

17:23.835 --> 17:25.461
DOWN INTO THE VENT NOW WOULD BE

17:25.586 --> 17:27.213
TO PUSH THE ENTIRE STATION OVER

17:27.338 --> 17:28.130
WITH IT.

17:28.255 --> 17:29.716
>> SOUNDS LIKE A PLAN TO ME.

17:29.841 --> 17:30.925
>> OUR RESCUE BOTS HAVE

17:31.050 --> 17:32.051
INCREDIBLE STRENGTH.

17:32.176 --> 17:33.594
IF WE ARM THE BOMB,  THEY  COULD

17:33.720 --> 17:35.179
PUSH THE LAB OVER THE LEDGE, AND

17:35.304 --> 17:36.597
CARRY ALL OF US BACK TO THE

17:36.723 --> 17:37.974
SURFACE IN PLENTY OF TIME.

17:38.098 --> 17:40.018
>> AND DESTROY MY HOME?

17:40.142 --> 17:42.436
YOU MOST CERTAINLY WILL NOT.

17:42.562 --> 17:43.980
>> BUT IT'S BASICALLY THE SAME

17:44.104 --> 17:45.523
PLAN YOU ORIGINALLY PROPOSED,

17:45.648 --> 17:46.524
ONLY --

17:46.649 --> 17:48.317
>> YOU KNOW NOTHING OF MY WORK.

17:48.442 --> 17:50.194
YOU KNOW NOTHING AT ALL.

17:50.319 --> 17:52.530
TAKE YOUR MECHANICAL MEN AND GO.

17:52.655 --> 17:55.700
ALL OF YOU! GET OUT!

17:55.825 --> 17:57.410
>> LET'S GO.

18:06.377 --> 18:08.922
>> YOU ARE NOT VERY GOOD AT

18:09.047 --> 18:11.257
LISTENING TO YOUR ELDERS, ARE

18:11.382 --> 18:12.675
YOU, CODY BURNS?

18:12.800 --> 18:14.802
>> UH, NO OFFENSE PROFESSOR, BUT

18:14.928 --> 18:16.012
NEITHER WERE YOU.

18:16.136 --> 18:18.014
>> [ LAUGHS ]

18:18.138 --> 18:19.557
INDEED.

18:19.682 --> 18:21.893
>> PROFESSOR, WHY DON'T YOU WANT

18:22.018 --> 18:24.896
TO COME BACK TO THE SURFACE?

18:25.021 --> 18:27.732
>> THIS IS MY WORLD NOW --

18:27.857 --> 18:32.070
PLANTS, OCEAN, RESEARCH.

18:32.194 --> 18:34.405
THE WORLD ABOVE, I-I FEAR

18:34.530 --> 18:36.574
EVERYTHING HAS CHANGED.

18:36.699 --> 18:38.284
>> YOU KNOW GRIFFIN ROCK.

18:38.409 --> 18:39.493
IT NEVER CHANGES.

18:39.619 --> 18:41.537
PEOPLE ARE STILL THE SAME, TOO,

18:41.662 --> 18:43.330
AND MOST OF THEM ARE REALLY

18:43.456 --> 18:44.290
NICE.

18:44.415 --> 18:45.583
I THINK YOU KNOW THAT, THOUGH.

18:45.708 --> 18:47.043
OTHERWISE, YOU WOULDN'T HAVE

18:47.167 --> 18:48.628
RISKED  EVERYTHING  TO TRY TO HELP

18:48.753 --> 18:49.587
THEM.

18:49.712 --> 18:50.296
DON'T YOU WANT TO FINISH WHAT

18:50.421 --> 18:51.130
YOU STARTED?

18:51.255 --> 18:53.424
>> YOUR FATHER WAS RIGHT.

18:53.549 --> 18:56.510
YOU ARE TENACIOUS.

19:00.556 --> 19:01.808
>> YOU, TAKE MY THINGS.

19:01.933 --> 19:03.559
ONCE THE BOMB IS SET, WE WILL

19:03.684 --> 19:05.144
HAVE 60 SECONDS TO PUSH THE

19:05.269 --> 19:06.562
STATION OVER THE CLIFF.

19:06.687 --> 19:08.439
CAN YOUR RESCUE MEN DO IT?

19:08.564 --> 19:10.066
>> YES, MA'AM.

19:10.190 --> 19:11.859
>> THE OLD MAN WILL STAY WITH ME

19:11.985 --> 19:13.319
TO SET THE BOMB'S TIMER.

19:13.444 --> 19:14.361
EVERYONE ELSE GO.

19:14.487 --> 19:16.196
>> OLD MAN?

19:16.322 --> 19:17.281
OH.

19:21.953 --> 19:23.329
>> ALL BOTS ARE READY, DAD.

19:23.454 --> 19:25.999
>>  ALL RIGHT, EVERYBODY, PUSH.

19:26.124 --> 19:27.416
[ ALL GRUNT ]

19:33.589 --> 19:36.843
>> GOOD. GOOD. STOP.

19:36.968 --> 19:39.804
OKAY, THE LAB IS IN POSITION.

19:41.472 --> 19:44.058
>> GOODBYE, MY MIDGARD.

19:44.183 --> 19:46.102
[ BEEPING ]

19:48.354 --> 19:51.941
>> ARMED AND EVACUATED. PROCEED.

19:57.488 --> 20:00.950
[ METAL CREAKING ]

20:09.333 --> 20:10.209
>> WE'RE JAMMED.

20:10.334 --> 20:13.379
EVERYONE, LIFT UP AND OVER.

20:13.504 --> 20:15.589
[ METAL CREAKING ]

20:15.715 --> 20:17.008
>> WHAT'S HAPPENING?

20:17.133 --> 20:18.926
>> OUR BOTS WILL TAKE CARE OF

20:19.052 --> 20:19.510
IT.

20:19.635 --> 20:21.888
[ BEEPING ]

20:22.013 --> 20:25.265
[ ALL GRUNTING ]

20:32.523 --> 20:33.149
GOOD JOB.

20:33.273 --> 20:36.027
NOW, GET US OUT OF HERE.

20:36.152 --> 20:37.361
[ BEEP ]

20:41.199 --> 20:43.034
[ BEEP ]

20:45.244 --> 20:47.121
[ BEEPING ]

20:57.256 --> 20:58.799
>> CONGRATULATIONS, PROFESSOR.

20:58.925 --> 21:02.970
YOU JUST SAVED A  LOT  OF LIVES.

21:03.096 --> 21:07.975
>> PROFESSOR, WELL, HERE IT IS.

21:08.101 --> 21:10.019
AND THIS IS WHAT IT WILL LOOK

21:10.144 --> 21:12.105
LIKE -- AN EXACT REPLICA BASED

21:12.230 --> 21:14.356
ON THE ORIGINAL DESIGNS FOR YOUR

21:14.481 --> 21:17.317
LAB SO YOU CAN FEEL AT HOME.

21:17.443 --> 21:18.778
IT'S GRIFFIN ROCK'S WAY OF

21:18.903 --> 21:20.487
SAYING, "THANKS," AND MY WAY OF

21:20.613 --> 21:23.824
SAYING, "WELCOME BACK."

21:23.950 --> 21:29.163
>> WOW. THANK YOU.

21:29.288 --> 21:32.750
>> I THINK HE LIKES HER.
